  "body": "### Description\r\nAs an implementor, I want fork versions and signature domains handled consistently so that there are no unexpected type/bounds inconsistencies and so that Artemis is compliant with the beacon chain spec. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* `Fork` field `previous_version` is a `bytes4` instead of `uint64`.\r\n* `Fork` field `current_version` is a `bytes4` instead of a `uint64`.\r\n* `BeaconStateUtil.get_fork_version` expects `Bytes` instead of `UnsignedLong` for `epoch`.\r\n* Ensure assignment to both `previous_version` and `current_version` in `get_genesis_beacon_state` performs `int_to_bytes4` on `GENESIS_FORK_VERSION` for type compatibility.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nSee https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/738\r\n\r\nI'm not immediately able to find where `get_genesis_beacon_state` is implemented and/or simulated in our code. @jrhea @dangerousfood \r\n",
